msgstr "says what is high to one who is low …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.12"
msgid "ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ—"
msgstr "says what is high to one who is high—one who is wise/one who is competent/one who is intelligent/one who is learned/one who is an expounder of the Teaching—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.13"
msgid "“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re wise/you’re competent/you’re intelligent/you’re learned/you’re an expounder of the Teaching/you’re not going to a bad destination/you can only expect a good destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of bad speech."

#. HTML: </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Not intending to abuse, indirect speech"

#. HTML: </h5><p>
#. REF: sc74, ms2V_102
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.14"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ na khuṃsetukāmo na vambhetukāmo na maṅkukattukāmo, davakamyatā evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, not wishing to revile, not wishing to insult, not wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, but wanting to have fun, says this, “There are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.15"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthi tesaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tesaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa."
msgstr "“There are wise ones/competent ones/intelligent ones/learned ones/expounders of the Teaching/those not going to a bad destination/those who can only expect a good destination, right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of bad speech."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc75, ms2V_103
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.16"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ na khuṃsetukāmo na vambhetukāmo na maṅkukattukāmo, davakamyatā evaṃ vadeti, “ye nūna caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, not wishing to revile, not wishing to insult, not wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, but wanting to have fun, says this, “Perhaps these are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:2.7.17"
msgid "“Ye nūna paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa."
